\begin_layout Section
Mixed Quantum–Classical Theory for electrodynamics
\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "sec:Mixed-Quantum–Classical-Theory"

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The section aims to compare Ehrenfest dynamics and exact quantum dynamics
 in the framework of mixed quantum–classical theory.
 First, we formulate the quantum-classical Liouville equations (QCLE) for
 quantum electrodynamics as formally exact equation of motion.
 Then, we approximate the probability density for Ehrenfest dynamics and
 derive the corresponding equation of motion.
 By comparing the equations of motion, we shall discover the difference.
\end_layout

